# =============================================================================
# Discord connector — LOCAL end-to-end env (placeholders only)
# =============================================================================
# Copy the values you need into apps/api/.env (the API + worker read .env;
# `discord:dev` reads it too via --env-file). This file is a per-var map of
# WHERE each value comes from in the Discord Developer Portal so a human can
# fill it without guessing. NEVER commit real values — only this template.
#
# Portal: https://discord.com/developers/applications  → your application
#
# Full ordered runbook (tunnel + portal + verify): docs/discord-e2e.md
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Public base URL (MUST be the cloudflared tunnel for E2E) -----------------
# Where: not from Discord — this is YOUR public https URL. For a local E2E it is
# the cloudflared quick-tunnel URL (https://<random>.trycloudflare.com). Discord
# PINGs the interactions endpoint synchronously when you save it, and the gateway
# worker forwards to ${API_PUBLIC_URL}/v1/connectors/discord/ingress — so it must
# be PUBLIC, not loopback. Set this BEFORE booting the API.
API_PUBLIC_URL=https://REPLACE-WITH-YOUR-TUNNEL.trycloudflare.com

# --- Gateway → ingress shared secret (engine env) -----------------------------
# Where: not from Discord — generate locally: openssl rand -base64 32
# Must be >=32 chars. The gateway worker sends it as `x-hogsend-ingress-secret`
# and the ingress route fail-CLOSES (401s) without it, so BOTH the API process
# and the gateway worker must see the SAME value.
CONNECTOR_INGRESS_SECRET=REPLACE_ME_run_openssl_rand_base64_32

# --- Discord application secrets ----------------------------------------------
# Bot tab → "Reset Token" → copy the token. Used for the Gateway login + bot
# REST. The three privileged intents (SERVER MEMBERS, MESSAGE CONTENT, PRESENCE)
# must ALSO be toggled ON on the Bot tab or login() rejects with disallowed
# intents. Read by the standalone gateway worker (discord:dev / discord:worker).
DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=your-bot-token

# OAuth2 tab → "Client ID" (same as the Application ID on General Information).
# Used to build the bot-install + member-link URLs and to identify the app.
DISCORD_APPLICATION_ID=your-application-id

# OAuth2 tab → "Client Secret" → "Reset Secret" to reveal. Server-side OAuth
# code exchange only (never sent to the browser).
DISCORD_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret

# General Information tab → "Public Key" (ed25519, hex). Verifies the signature
# on every interactions POST, including Discord's validation PING when you save
# the Interactions Endpoint URL. The connector is only registered when this +
# DISCORD_APPLICATION_ID + DISCORD_CLIENT_SECRET are all set.
DISCORD_PUBLIC_KEY=your-public-key-hex

# OAuth2 tab → set after the bot is installed into your server. Optional mirror
# of the guild the bot joined (the install callback also captures it into the
# derived credential). Right-click your server icon in Discord with Developer
# Mode on → "Copy Server ID".
# DISCORD_GUILD_ID=
